// useEditorHistory
// Manages undo/redo state for a CodeMirror editor instance.

canUndo and canRedo are kept in sync by listening to every transaction on the editor.
The editor reference is managed externally via setEditor so the hook can be used with
editor instances that mount/unmount independently.

FUNCTION useEditorHistory() -> { editorRef, setEditor, undo, redo, canUndo, canRedo }  EXPORT
  Manages state: canUndo, canRedo.
  Holds a ref to the current EditorView instance.

---

FUNCTION setEditor(view)
  Stores the EditorView reference.
  IF view is null, clears canUndo and canRedo.
  IF view is provided, attaches an update listener that calls updateHistoryState after every
  document change or transaction, and sets initial undo/redo state.

---

FUNCTION updateHistoryState(view)
  Reads undoDepth and redoDepth from the editor state and updates canUndo/canRedo accordingly.

---

FUNCTION undo()
  Calls the CodeMirror undo command on the current editor, if canUndo is true.

---

FUNCTION redo()
  Calls the CodeMirror redo command on the current editor, if canRedo is true.
